{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"When I was growing up in Montana,"},{"time":4000,"text":"I had two dreams."},{"time":7000,"text":"I wanted to be a paleontologist,"},{"time":9000,"text":"a dinosaur paleontologist,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and I wanted to have a pet dinosaur."},{"time":14000,"text":"And so that's what I've been striving for"},{"time":17000,"text":"all of my life."},{"time":20000,"text":"I was very fortunate"},{"time":22000,"text":"early in my career."},{"time":24000,"text":"I was fortunate"},{"time":26000,"text":"in finding things."},{"time":28000,"text":"I wasn't very good at reading things."},{"time":30000,"text":"In fact, I don't read much of anything."},{"time":33000,"text":"I am extremely dyslexic,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and so reading is the hardest thing I do."},{"time":38000,"text":"But instead, I go out and I find things."},{"time":41000,"text":"Then I just pick things up."},{"time":43000,"text":"I basically practice for finding money on the street."},{"time":46000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":48000,"text":"And I wander about the hills,"},{"time":50000,"text":"and I have found a few things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53000,"text":"And I have been fortunate enough"},{"time":56000,"text":"to find things like the first eggs in the Western hemisphere"},{"time":61000,"text":"and the first baby dinosaurs in nests,"},{"time":65000,"text":"the first dinosaur embryos"},{"time":67000,"text":"and massive accumulations of bones."},{"time":71000,"text":"And it happened to be at a time"},{"time":73000,"text":"when people were just starting to begin to realize"},{"time":77000,"text":"that dinosaurs weren't the big, stupid, green reptiles"},{"time":81000,"text":"that people had thought for so many years."},{"time":84000,"text":"People were starting to get an idea"},{"time":86000,"text":"that dinosaurs were special."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"And so, at that time,"},{"time":91000,"text":"I was able to make some interesting hypotheses"},{"time":94000,"text":"along with my colleagues."},{"time":96000,"text":"We were able to actually say"},{"time":98000,"text":"that dinosaurs -- based on the evidence we had --"},{"time":101000,"text":"that dinosaurs built nests"},{"time":104000,"text":"and lived in colonies"},{"time":107000,"text":"and cared for their young,"},{"time":109000,"text":"brought food to their babies"},{"time":111000,"text":"and traveled in gigantic herds."},{"time":114000,"text":"So it was pretty interesting stuff."},{"time":117000,"text":"I have gone on to find more things"},{"time":120000,"text":"and discover that dinosaurs really were very social."},{"time":124000,"text":"We have found a lot of evidence"},{"time":127000,"text":"that dinosaurs changed"},{"time":129000,"text":"from when they were juveniles to when they were adults."},{"time":131000,"text":"The appearance of them would have been different --"},{"time":134000,"text":"which it is in all social animals."},{"time":136000,"text":"In social groups of animals,"},{"time":138000,"text":"the juveniles always look different than the adults."},{"time":141000,"text":"The adults can recognize the juveniles;"},{"time":143000,"text":"the juveniles can recognize the adults."},{"time":145000,"text":"And so we're making a better picture"},{"time":148000,"text":"of what a dinosaur looks like."},{"time":150000,"text":"And they didn't just all chase Jeeps around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":155000,"text":"But it is that social thing"},{"time":158000,"text":"that I guess attracted Michael Crichton."},{"time":162000,"text":"And in his book, he talked about the social animals."},{"time":166000,"text":"And then Steven Spielberg, of course,"},{"time":168000,"text":"depicts these dinosaurs"},{"time":170000,"text":"as being very social creatures."},{"time":173000,"text":"The theme of this story is building a dinosaur,"},{"time":175000,"text":"and so we come to that part of \"Jurassic Park.\""},{"time":179000,"text":"Michael Crichton really was one of the first people"},{"time":182000,"text":"to talk about bringing dinosaurs back to life."},{"time":186000,"text":"You all know the story, right."},{"time":188000,"text":"I mean, I assume everyone here has seen \"Jurassic Park.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"If you want to make a dinosaur,"},{"time":193000,"text":"you go out, you find yourself a piece of petrified tree sap --"},{"time":197000,"text":"otherwise known as amber --"},{"time":199000,"text":"that has some blood-sucking insects in it,"},{"time":202000,"text":"good ones,"},{"time":204000,"text":"and you get your insect and you drill into it"},{"time":207000,"text":"and you suck out some DNA,"},{"time":209000,"text":"because obviously all insects that sucked blood in those days"},{"time":212000,"text":"sucked dinosaur DNA out."},{"time":215000,"text":"And you take your DNA back to the laboratory"},{"time":218000,"text":"and you clone it."},{"time":221000,"text":"And I guess you inject it into maybe an ostrich egg,"},{"time":224000,"text":"or something like that,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and then you wait,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and, lo and behold, out pops a little baby dinosaur."},{"time":231000,"text":"And everybody's happy about that."},{"time":234000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":237000,"text":"And they're happy over and over again."},{"time":239000,"text":"They keep doing it; they just keep making these things."},{"time":242000,"text":"And then, then, then, and then ..."},{"time":246000,"text":"Then the dinosaurs, being social,"},{"time":249000,"text":"act out their socialness,"},{"time":252000,"text":"and they get together,"},{"time":254000,"text":"and they conspire."},{"time":257000,"text":"And, of course, that's what makes Steven Spielberg's movie --"},{"time":261000,"text":"conspiring dinosaurs chasing people around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264000,"text":"So I assume everybody knows"},{"time":266000,"text":"that if you actually had a piece of amber and it had an insect in it,"},{"time":269000,"text":"and you drilled into it,"},{"time":272000,"text":"and you got something out of that insect,"},{"time":274000,"text":"and you cloned it, and you did it over and over and over again,"},{"time":277000,"text":"you'd have a room full of mosquitos."},{"time":279000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":281000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":286000,"text":"And probably a whole bunch of trees as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289000,"text":"Now if you want dinosaur DNA,"},{"time":291000,"text":"I say go to the dinosaur."},{"time":294000,"text":"So that's what we've done."},{"time":296000,"text":"Back in 1993 when the movie came out,"},{"time":298000,"text":"we actually had a grant from the National Science Foundation"},{"time":301000,"text":"to attempt to extract DNA from a dinosaur,"},{"time":304000,"text":"and we chose the dinosaur on the left,"},{"time":307000,"text":"a Tyrannosaurus rex, which was a very nice specimen."},{"time":310000,"text":"And one of my former doctoral students,"},{"time":312000,"text":"Dr. Mary Schweitzer,"},{"time":314000,"text":"actually had the background"},{"time":316000,"text":"to do this sort of thing."},{"time":318000,"text":"And so she looked into the bone of this T. rex,"},{"time":321000,"text":"one of the thigh bones,"},{"time":323000,"text":"and she actually found"},{"time":325000,"text":"some very interesting structures in there."},{"time":328000,"text":"They found these red circular-looking objects,"},{"time":332000,"text":"and they looked, for all the world,"},{"time":334000,"text":"like red blood cells."},{"time":336000,"text":"And they're in"},{"time":338000,"text":"what appear to be the blood channels"},{"time":340000,"text":"that go through the bone."},{"time":342000,"text":"And so she thought, well, what the heck."},{"time":345000,"text":"So she sampled some material out of it."},{"time":348000,"text":"Now it wasn't DNA; she didn't find DNA."},{"time":351000,"text":"But she did find heme,"},{"time":354000,"text":"which is the biological foundation"},{"time":356000,"text":"of hemoglobin."},{"time":358000,"text":"And that was really cool."},{"time":360000,"text":"That was interesting."},{"time":362000,"text":"That was -- here we have 65-million-year-old heme."},{"time":367000,"text":"Well we tried and tried"},{"time":369000,"text":"and we couldn't really get anything else out of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371000,"text":"So a few years went by,"},{"time":373000,"text":"and then we started the Hell Creek Project."},{"time":375000,"text":"And the Hell Creek Project was this massive undertaking"},{"time":378000,"text":"to get as many dinosaurs as we could possibly find,"},{"time":381000,"text":"and hopefully find some dinosaurs"},{"time":383000,"text":"that had more material in them."},{"time":386000,"text":"And out in eastern Montana"},{"time":389000,"text":"there's a lot of space, a lot of badlands,"},{"time":391000,"text":"and not very many people,"},{"time":393000,"text":"and so you can go out there and find a lot of stuff."},{"time":395000,"text":"And we did find a lot of stuff."},{"time":397000,"text":"We found a lot of Tyrannosaurs,"},{"time":399000,"text":"but we found one special Tyrannosaur,"},{"time":401000,"text":"and we called it B-rex."},{"time":403000,"text":"And B-rex was found"},{"time":405000,"text":"under a thousand cubic yards of rock."},{"time":407000,"text":"It wasn't a very complete T. rex,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and it wasn't a very big T. rex,"},{"time":413000,"text":"but it was a very special B-rex."},{"time":416000,"text":"And I and my colleagues cut into it,"},{"time":418000,"text":"and we were able to determine,"},{"time":420000,"text":"by looking at lines of arrested growth, some lines in it,"},{"time":423000,"text":"that B-rex had died at the age of 16."},{"time":426000,"text":"We don't really know how long dinosaurs lived,"},{"time":429000,"text":"because we haven't found the oldest one yet."},{"time":431000,"text":"But this one died at the age of 16."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"We gave samples to Mary Schweitzer,"},{"time":436000,"text":"and she was actually able to determine"},{"time":438000,"text":"that B-rex was a female"},{"time":440000,"text":"based on medullary tissue"},{"time":442000,"text":"found on the inside of the bone."},{"time":444000,"text":"Medullary tissue is the calcium build-up,"},{"time":447000,"text":"the calcium storage basically,"},{"time":449000,"text":"when an animal is pregnant,"},{"time":451000,"text":"when a bird is pregnant."},{"time":453000,"text":"So here was the character"},{"time":455000,"text":"that linked birds and dinosaurs."},{"time":457000,"text":"But Mary went further."},{"time":459000,"text":"She took the bone, and she dumped it into acid."},{"time":462000,"text":"Now we all know that bones are fossilized,"},{"time":465000,"text":"and so if you dump it into acid,"},{"time":467000,"text":"there shouldn't be anything left."},{"time":469000,"text":"But there was something left."},{"time":471000,"text":"There were blood vessels left."},{"time":474000,"text":"There were flexible, clear blood vessels."},{"time":478000,"text":"And so here was the first soft tissue from a dinosaur."},{"time":481000,"text":"It was extraordinary."},{"time":483000,"text":"But she also found osteocytes,"},{"time":486000,"text":"which are the cells that laid down the bones."},{"time":489000,"text":"And try and try, we could not find DNA,"},{"time":493000,"text":"but she did find evidence of proteins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"But we thought maybe --"},{"time":499000,"text":"well, we thought maybe"},{"time":501000,"text":"that the material was breaking down after it was coming out of the ground."},{"time":504000,"text":"We thought maybe it was deteriorating very fast."},{"time":506000,"text":"And so we built a laboratory"},{"time":508000,"text":"in the back of an 18-wheeler trailer,"},{"time":511000,"text":"and actually took the laboratory to the field"},{"time":514000,"text":"where we could get better samples."},{"time":516000,"text":"And we did. We got better material."},{"time":519000,"text":"The cells looked better."},{"time":521000,"text":"The vessels looked better."},{"time":523000,"text":"Found the protein collagen."},{"time":525000,"text":"I mean, it was wonderful stuff."},{"time":528000,"text":"But it's not dinosaur DNA."},{"time":532000,"text":"So we have discovered"},{"time":534000,"text":"that dinosaur DNA, and all DNA,"},{"time":536000,"text":"just breaks down too fast."},{"time":538000,"text":"We're just not going to be able"},{"time":540000,"text":"to do what they did in \"Jurassic Park.\""},{"time":543000,"text":"We're not going to be able to make a dinosaur"},{"time":546000,"text":"based on a dinosaur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"But birds are dinosaurs."},{"time":554000,"text":"Birds are living dinosaurs."},{"time":557000,"text":"We actually classify them"},{"time":559000,"text":"as dinosaurs."},{"time":561000,"text":"We now call them non-avian dinosaurs"},{"time":563000,"text":"and avian dinosaurs."},{"time":565000,"text":"So the non-avian dinosaurs"},{"time":567000,"text":"are the big clunky ones that went extinct."},{"time":569000,"text":"Avian dinosaurs are our modern birds."},{"time":572000,"text":"So we don't have to make a dinosaur"},{"time":574000,"text":"because we already have them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"I know, you're as bad as the sixth-graders."},{"time":587000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":589000,"text":"The sixth-graders look at it and they say, \"No.\""},{"time":592000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":594000,"text":"\"You can call it a dinosaur,"},{"time":596000,"text":"but look at the velociraptor: the velociraptor is cool.\""},{"time":599000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":601000,"text":"\"The chicken is not.\""},{"time":603000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":605000,"text":"So this is our problem,"},{"time":607000,"text":"as you can imagine."},{"time":610000,"text":"The chicken is a dinosaur."},{"time":612000,"text":"I mean it really is."},{"time":614000,"text":"You can't argue with it"},{"time":616000,"text":"because we're the classifiers and we've classified it that way."},{"time":619000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":621000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":626000,"text":"But the sixth-graders demand it."},{"time":628000,"text":"\"Fix the chicken.\""},{"time":630000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":632000,"text":"So that's what I'm here to tell you about:"},{"time":634000,"text":"how we are going to fix a chicken."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"So we have a number of ways"},{"time":640000,"text":"that we actually can fix the chicken."},{"time":645000,"text":"Because evolution works,"},{"time":647000,"text":"we actually have some evolutionary tools."},{"time":650000,"text":"We'll call them biological modification tools."},{"time":653000,"text":"We have selection."},{"time":655000,"text":"And we know selection works."},{"time":657000,"text":"We started out with a wolf-like creature"},{"time":660000,"text":"and we ended up with a Maltese."},{"time":663000,"text":"I mean, that's --"},{"time":666000,"text":"that's definitely genetic modification."},{"time":670000,"text":"Or any of the other funny-looking little dogs."},{"time":675000,"text":"We also have transgenesis."},{"time":677000,"text":"Transgenesis is really cool too."},{"time":679000,"text":"That's where you take a gene out of one animal and stick it in another one."},{"time":682000,"text":"That's how people make GloFish."},{"time":685000,"text":"You take a glow gene"},{"time":688000,"text":"out of a coral or a jellyfish"},{"time":692000,"text":"and you stick it in a zebrafish,"},{"time":694000,"text":"and, puff, they glow."},{"time":696000,"text":"And that's pretty cool."},{"time":698000,"text":"And they obviously make a lot of money off of them."},{"time":701000,"text":"And now they're making Glow-rabbits"},{"time":703000,"text":"and Glow-all-sorts-of-things."},{"time":705000,"text":"I guess we could make a glow chicken."},{"time":708000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":710000,"text":"But I don't think that'll satisfy the sixth-graders either."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713000,"text":"But there's another thing."},{"time":715000,"text":"There's what we call atavism activation."},{"time":718000,"text":"And atavism activation"},{"time":720000,"text":"is basically --"},{"time":722000,"text":"an atavism is an ancestral characteristic."},{"time":726000,"text":"You heard"},{"time":728000,"text":"that occasionally children are born with tails,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and it's because it's an ancestral characteristic."},{"time":735000,"text":"And so there are a number of atavisms"},{"time":738000,"text":"that can happen."},{"time":740000,"text":"Snakes are occasionally born with legs."},{"time":743000,"text":"And here's an example."},{"time":745000,"text":"This is a chicken with teeth."},{"time":748000,"text":"A fellow by the name of Matthew Harris"},{"time":750000,"text":"at the University of Wisconsin in Madison"},{"time":753000,"text":"actually figured out a way to stimulate"},{"time":756000,"text":"the gene for teeth,"},{"time":759000,"text":"and so was able to actually turn the tooth gene on"},{"time":762000,"text":"and produce teeth in chickens."},{"time":765000,"text":"Now that's a good characteristic."},{"time":768000,"text":"We can save that one."},{"time":771000,"text":"We know we can use that."},{"time":773000,"text":"We can make a chicken with teeth."},{"time":777000,"text":"That's getting closer."},{"time":779000,"text":"That's better than a glowing chicken."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"A friend of mine, a colleague of mine,"},{"time":785000,"text":"Dr. Hans Larsson at McGill University,"},{"time":787000,"text":"is actually looking at atavisms."},{"time":789000,"text":"And he's looking at them"},{"time":791000,"text":"by looking at the embryo genesis of birds"},{"time":794000,"text":"and actually looking at how they develop,"},{"time":797000,"text":"and he's interested in how birds actually lost their tail."},{"time":801000,"text":"He's also interested in the transformation"},{"time":803000,"text":"of the arm, the hand, to the wing."},{"time":806000,"text":"He's looking for those genes as well."},{"time":808000,"text":"And I said, \"Well, if you can find those,"},{"time":811000,"text":"I can just reverse them"},{"time":813000,"text":"and make what I need to make for the sixth-graders.\""},{"time":816000,"text":"And so he agreed."},{"time":818000,"text":"And so that's what we're looking into."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820000,"text":"If you look at dinosaur hands,"},{"time":822000,"text":"a velociraptor"},{"time":824000,"text":"has that cool-looking hand with the claws on it."},{"time":826000,"text":"Archaeopteryx, which is a bird, a primitive bird,"},{"time":829000,"text":"still has that very primitive hand."},{"time":832000,"text":"But as you can see, the pigeon,"},{"time":834000,"text":"or a chicken or anything else, another bird,"},{"time":836000,"text":"has kind of a weird-looking hand,"},{"time":839000,"text":"because the hand is a wing."},{"time":841000,"text":"But the cool thing is"},{"time":843000,"text":"that, if you look in the embryo,"},{"time":846000,"text":"as the embryo is developing"},{"time":848000,"text":"the hand actually looks"},{"time":851000,"text":"pretty much like the archaeopteryx hand."},{"time":853000,"text":"It has the three fingers, the three digits."},{"time":856000,"text":"But a gene turns on that actually fuses those together."},{"time":859000,"text":"And so what we're looking for is that gene."},{"time":862000,"text":"We want to stop that gene from turning on,"},{"time":864000,"text":"fusing those hands together,"},{"time":866000,"text":"so we can get a chicken that hatches out with a three-fingered hand,"},{"time":869000,"text":"like the archaeopteryx."},{"time":871000,"text":"And the same goes for the tails."},{"time":874000,"text":"Birds have basically"},{"time":877000,"text":"rudimentary tails."},{"time":879000,"text":"And so we know"},{"time":882000,"text":"that in embryo,"},{"time":884000,"text":"as the animal is developing,"},{"time":886000,"text":"it actually has a relatively long tail."},{"time":889000,"text":"But a gene turns on"},{"time":891000,"text":"and resorbs the tail, gets rid of it."},{"time":894000,"text":"So that's the other gene we're looking for."},{"time":897000,"text":"We want to stop that tail from resorbing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"So what we're trying to do really"},{"time":904000,"text":"is take our chicken,"},{"time":907000,"text":"modify it"},{"time":909000,"text":"and make the chickenosaurus."},{"time":911000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":914000,"text":"It's a cooler-looking chicken."},{"time":917000,"text":"But it's just the very basics."},{"time":920000,"text":"So that really is what we're doing."},{"time":922000,"text":"And people always say, \"Why do that?"},{"time":924000,"text":"Why make this thing?"},{"time":926000,"text":"What good is it?\""},{"time":928000,"text":"Well, that's a good question."},{"time":930000,"text":"Actually, I think it's a great way to teach kids"},{"time":932000,"text":"about evolutionary biology"},{"time":934000,"text":"and developmental biology"},{"time":936000,"text":"and all sorts of things."},{"time":938000,"text":"And quite frankly, I think"},{"time":941000,"text":"if Colonel Sanders"},{"time":943000,"text":"was to be careful how he worded it,"},{"time":946000,"text":"he could actually advertise an extra piece."},{"time":949000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":953000,"text":"Anyway --"},{"time":957000,"text":"When our dino-chicken hatches,"},{"time":961000,"text":"it will be, obviously, the poster child,"},{"time":964000,"text":"or what you might call a poster chick,"},{"time":967000,"text":"for technology, entertainment and design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}